the story using interviews with prominent academic psychiatrists in Canada and the United States, and describes his own experiences as a psychiatrist: how he was caught up in the excitement of the psychoanalytic model, how he became disillusioned with it, and how he came to a new and more scientific view of his discipline. This is an essential work for understanding the recent history of psychiatry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPsychiatryzCanadaxHistory. 0aPsychiatryzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPsychoanalysiszCanadaxHistory. 0aPsychoanalysiszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Psychoanalysis.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268124840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442681248423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442681248.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK